  }
}

notes: |md
  **Key Design Decisions:**

  1. Magic string "REDIS0011" identifies valid RDB files
  2. Type opcodes identify data structure (string/list/set/hash)
  3. Varint length encoding minimizes file size
  4. Expiration stored before key-value for lazy check during load
  5. CRC64 provides end-to-end integrity checking
  6. Binary-safe: length prefixes instead of null-terminators

  **Memory Boundaries:**
  - Cache line: 64B (dashed lines where applicable)
  - Page: 4096B (bold lines where applicable)
  - File layout optimized for sequential read during LOAD
| {
  near: top-right
  style.font-size: 12
  style.fill: white
  style.border-radius: 8
}